Source: halos-browser-trust
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Matti Airas <matti.airas@hatlabs.fi>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/halos-org/halos-browser-trust
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: halos-browser-trust
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, libnss3, p11-kit-modules
Description: Make NSS applications trust the system CA store
 Bridges NSS to the system p11-kit trust store by diverting libnssckbi.so to
 p11-kit-trust.so, the standard mechanism Fedora and Arch enable by default but
 Debian omits.
 .
 Without this, NSS-based applications (Chromium, Firefox) on a HaLOS desktop
 trust only the static Mozilla root bundle and ignore CAs installed into the
 system trust store via update-ca-certificates. With it, the on-device browser
 trusts the device's own auto-CA (and any operator-installed CA) with no manual
 per-user steps. Pulled in by the halos-desktop metapackage, so it lands only on
 desktop variants.
